2r&=\sqrt{(3-(-1))^2+2^2}\\
\Rightarrow\qquad r&=\frac{\sqrt{16+4}}{2}=\frac{2\sqrt{5}}{2}=\sqrt{5}
\end{align*}Therefore, the area of the circle is given by \begin{align*}
\pi r^2&=\pi(\sqrt{5})^2\\
&=\boxed{5\pi}.
\end{align*}
